description: Similarities and differences in the last three major conflicts between Israel and Hamas.
title: In Gaza, a Pattern of Conflict
title_page: In Gaza, a Pattern of Conflict - The New York Times
maintext:
2014
Day 14 of 24
Mr. Kerry arrives in Cairo to work on a cease-fire, but the situation is more challenging than in 2012. With the ouster of Mr. Morsi, Egypt is seen as more aligned with Israel. As a result, Mr. Kerry turns to Qatar and Turkey as alternative mediators, a move that some say makes the United States appear less supportive of Israel.
